Initialize `ec` in Triangulate: the v2.0.1 tag leaves it uninitialized, which
GCC's -Wmaybe-uninitialized promotes to an error under Clipper2's own -Werror.
Matches the fix already on upstream main.

diff --git before/Clipper2/CPP/Clipper2Lib/src/clipper.triangulation.cpp after/Clipper2/CPP/Clipper2Lib/src/clipper.triangulation.cpp
--- before/Clipper2/CPP/Clipper2Lib/src/clipper.triangulation.cpp
+++ after/Clipper2/CPP/Clipper2Lib/src/clipper.triangulation.cpp
@@ -1202,7 +1202,7 @@

   TriangulateResult Triangulate(const PathsD& pp, int decPlaces, PathsD& solution, bool useDelaunay)
   {
-    int ec;
+    int ec = 0;
     double scale;
     TriangulateResult result;
     if (decPlaces <= 0) scale = 1;
